Intuit to connect its software to Internet . Intuit Inc said Monday it plans to open up its software products for direct access to the Internet , in moves designed to accelerate the exchange of financial data between customers and banks . The company said the new Internet initiative will give financial institutions direct acccess to their customers over the Internet via its products , including its flagship Quicken personal financial software . It said the capability will arrive in stages beginning with a capacity to exchange investment data , which is expected to become available next spring . In addition , Intuit said it plans to offer financial service providers a series of software specifications to give banks and other such institutions full control over their electronic communications with customers . It said these specifications , to be known as OpenExchange , will be licensed for free and without restriction to financial service providers . The company said the OpenExchange guidelines will enable the secure exchange via the Internet of banking and investment data , bill paying and other financial transactions and services . Intuit said the comprehensive specifications will support a full range of financial interactions between financial service providers and their customers . Rival approaches focus primarily on checking account transactions . It said OpenExchange will embrace top industry security methods such as RSA data encryption for secure communications and authentication of the respective parties in a transaction . Intuit said OpenExchange will also cover data exchange between customers and government agencies - - an apparent reference to Intuit ' s tax preparation software products . Intuit said that after working in conjunction with its technology partners , transaction processing companies and financial service institutions , it plans to publish the OpenExchange framework by the end of 1996 . Intuit also announced plans sell its bill payment processing subsidiary to CheckFree Corp in exchange for 12 . 6 million CheckFree shares , or about 23 percent of the CheckFree shares outstanding . Intuit said the move allows it to reallocate management and financial resources to its growing emphasis on the Internet and its successful core businesses . - - Eric Auchard , New York Newsdesk 212 - 859 - 1736 
